Condition : 1 - The development hereby permitted shall begin not later than three years from the date of this decision.
Condition : 2 - The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans and specifications: [Fire Strategy Report, Confirmation of ownership dated on 31/1/2024 and Construction Method Statement for the Basement. Received: 7/2/2024
Letter from Dannie Walton about the Chinese takeaway business. Received: 15/3/2024 
Energy Statement, Summary for Input Data (lean), Summary for Input Data (green) and Summary for Input Data (base). Received: 10/4/2024
Triple Glazed Windows brochure, Documents about proposed materials for boundary wall and Noise Impact Assessment. Received: 22/4/2024
Unnumbered Location Plan, LIVARCH/40BRS/101-B, LIVARCH/40BRS/102-D, LIVARCH/40BRS/103-A, LIVARCH/40BRS/104-D, LIVARCH/40BRS/105-A, LIVARCH/40BRS/106-C, LIVARCH/40BRS/109-A, LIVARCH/40BRS/110-A, LIVARCH/40BRS/111-A, Planning Statement V2 and Heritage Statement and Statement for Proposed material. Received: 3/6/2024 
LIVARCH/40BRS/107-C and LIVARCH/40BRS/108-E. Received: 6/6/2024 ].
Reason: In order to ensure the development is carried out in accordance with the planning permission.
Condition : 3 - The materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted shall match those used in the existing building, unless otherwise shown on the approved plans. Reason: In order to safeguard the appearance of the area.
Condition : 4 - The basement hereby permitted shall at no time be used or occupied as a separate dwelling independent of the main house and shall not be used as sleeping accommodation.
Reason: In order to ensure that adequate living standards are maintained and to protect neighbours' living conditions.
Condition : 5 - The windows to be fitted on the front roof face of the dwelling shall be black-framed and traditional, conservation-style.
Reason: In order to safeguard the architectural and historic interest of the conservation area.
Condition : 6 - No development shall take place until a Construction Logistics Plan (CLP), written in accordance with current TfL guidance, has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The CLP shall include: 

(a)	a site plan (showing the elements set out below);
(b)	confirmation that a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway will be undertaken with Hounslow Highways and a commitment to repair any damage caused;
(c)	provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors;
(d)	provisions for loading, unloading and storage of plant and materials within the site;
(e)	details of access to the site, including means to control and manage access and egress of vehicles to and from the site for the duration of construction including phasing arrangements;
(f)	details of vehicle routeing from the site to the wider strategic road network;
(g)	the erection and maintenance of security hoarding including decorative displays and facilities for public viewing, where appropriate;
(h)	provision of wheel washing facilities at the site exit and a commitment to sweep adjacent roads when required and at the request of the Council;
(i)	a scheme for recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works; 
(j)	measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway especially cyclists and pedestrians in the vicinity of the site and especially at the access;
(k)	commitment to liaise with other contractors in the vicinity of the site to maximise the potential for consolidation and to minimise traffic impacts;
(l)	avoidance of peak hours for deliveries and details of a booking system to avoid vehicles waiting on the public highway;
(m)	all necessary traffic orders and other permissions required to allow safe access to the site to be secured and implemented prior to commencement of construction;
(n)	details of the construction programme and a schedule of traffic movements;
(o)	the use of o
Condition : 7 - The basement should be built in accordance to the submitted Construction Method Statement (CMS) throughout the construction period for the development.
Reason: In order to protect the living conditions of neighbouring residents, to minimise flood risk and to ensure highway safety is maintained.
Condition : 8 - No dwelling shall be occupied until spaces has been laid out within the site in accordance with approved plan for bicycles to be parked and that space shall thereafter be kept available for the parking of bicycles; prior to commencement of the use.
Reason: In order to support sustainable transport objectives.
Condition : 9 - The existing vehicular access to the side boundary shall not be used by vehicles and the footway should be reinstated before the development hereby permitted is first occupied or brought into use, 
Reason: In order to enhance the pedestrian environment and to confine vehicular access to the permitted points in order to ensure that the development does not prejudice the free flow of traffic or highway safety along the adjacent highway.
Condition : 10 - The cumulative measured or calculated rating level of noise emitted from the Air Source Heat Pumps (ASHP) to which this permission refers, shall follow the submitted noise impact report at all times that the plant operate. 
Reason: In order to protect neighbours' living conditions.
Condition : 11 - Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development Order) 1995 (or any order revoking or re-enacting that order), no enlargement of the premises or any additional structures/buildings/enclosures within the curtilage of the site shall be carried out, other than as shown in the approved drawings, and no additional floor space shall be formed within the building(s) hereby permitted by means of internal horizontal division (new mezzanine level) without prior written approval of the local planning authority.
Reason:  To protect neighbours' living conditions and the character and appearance of the area and to prevent over-intensive use of the site.
